    "media:imagetext": "1,000 Bonus Miles\nplus expanded Alaska\nand West Coast\nService.\nExpanded service\n› A new agreement between Northwest Airlines and\nAlaska Airlines covers 37 cities throughout the U.S.,\nCanada, Mexico, the Caribbean, Asia and Europe,\nwith over 280 flights daily effective 10/29/95.\nOur new coordinated system offers one-stop\ncheck-in; boarding passes, seat assignments and\nautomated baggage tags to final destination,\nplus automatic WorldPerks® mileage credits.\nBonus Miles\n• Earn 500 WorldPerks Bonus Miles on each qualifying\nflight segment on Alaska Airlines, Horizon Air or\nNorthwest designated flights (7000-7999), plus\nMinneapolis/St. Paul-Anchorage daily nonstop flight\nbetween October 29, 1995 and January 31, 1996.\nEnhanced benefits to WorldPerks members\nv WorldPerks members also earn a minimum of\n500 WorldPerks miles per flight segment on\nAlaska Airlines. Preferred members are eligible\nfor an additional 25% credit and Gold members\nreceive a 100% bonus.\nFor reservations, and complete details on\nWorldPerks Program and Bonus Miles, call your\ntravel professional or Northwest Airlines at\n1-800-225-2525.\n©1995 Northwest Airlines, Inc.\nNorthwest recycles enough paper products in one year to save over 26,000 trees.",
